  "text": "The new classification includes the presence of impairments performing complex ADL, but not sufficiently severe to affect functional independence. The previous classification of MCI did not include difficulties performing ADL, only mild cognitive deficits caused by factors other than aging. Moreover, these deficits must be documented by objective testing and MCI patients should exhibit no signs of dementia [CITATION_1] . Impairments in ADL may be secondary to cognitive problems or to other limitations present in elderly individuals.",
